      "message": "I think I know what\u0027s happening here (we always create the VarDeclaration as soon as the Var is instantiated, right?). Maybe just explain that in the comment.\n\nAlso: Do we want to try and report this (C++) misuse as an error? eg, if someone *does* declare a var, and then also include it in a parameter list, we could try to fail more gracefully? I don\u0027t think it\u0027s necessary - that\u0027s the kind of static code structure error that needs to be fixed at the call-site, just a thought.",
