      "side": 1,
      "message": "Note: I wrote the remainder of this comment before Brian added his comment explaining that I should do... you know... exactly this.\n\n---\n\nIn order to fix the issue of variables being accessed before their declarations due to a lack of ordering guarantees in C++, https://skia-review.googlesource.com/c/skia/+/380358 made it so that variables create their declaration statements at creation time.\n\nFor parameters, this declaration statement goes unused, and its late destruction was causing a crash with this change. The \"hasn\u0027t been declared yet\" just meant \"not declared prior to this point, because this (adding it as a function parameter) counts as declaring it even though we aren\u0027t explicitly doing so\". I will reword that comment to be less confusing.\n\nNow that I think about it, we should be checking that parameters were not specified with values and that variables either get declared or used as function parameters prior to destruction. Adding a couple error checks around this.",
